b.com/person/101582/","id":101582,"name":"Dana Wilkerson"},{"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/person/101584/","id":101584,"name":"Keith Neubert"},{"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/person/101589/","id":101589,"name":"Antwahn Nance"}],"description":"<p>Slam City with Scottie Pippen is an FMV-based basketball game and may very well represent the over saturation of FMV games. You play as rookie streetballer and you must fight your way up the food chain to reach Scottie Pippen. The gameplay, as one might expect, is rather bizarre: You play the game from a behind-the-back perspective with a video running in the foreground of a basketball game. Although the game attempts to make itself feel like a third person game, it most obviously isn't: it's merely a sprite cutout placed in front of a video of a guy filming a basketball game in first-person. Your opponent will attempt to steal the ball from you or block your shots. You must dodge these attempts and wait for the opportunity to score. Because of the limitation of the FMV format, you can only score at predetermined points indicated by certain movements from your opponent. After every attempt to score, the game cuts away to show activities of the various onlookers.</p>","releases":[{"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/release/84301/","id":84301,"name":"Slam City with Scottie Pippen"},{"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/release/84302/","id":84302,"name":"Slam City with Scottie Pippen"}],"franchises":[],"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/game/33/","number_of_user_reviews":0,"objects":[{"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/object/438/","site_detail_url":"http://www.giantbomb.com/basketball/93-438/","id":438,"name":"Basketball"},{"api_detail_url":"http://api.giantbomb.com/object/831/","site_detail_url":"http://www.giantbomb.com/sports-jersey/93-831/","id":831,"name":"Sports Jersey"}],"original_game_rating":null,"date_added":"2008-04-01 01:32:55","first_appearance_concepts":[],"na